{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PRACH scheduling in TDD mixed slots\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_ue_prach_scheduler` function was incorrectly scheduling PRACH transmissions in TDD mixed slots where the PRACH symbols were not within the UL portion of the slot. This was causing resource block allocation violations downstream.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ue_scheduler.c`: Added validation in `nr_ue_prach_scheduler` to ensure PRACH symbols are within the UL portion of mixed slots in TDD configurations.\n\n### Reproduction\nIn TDD configurations with mixed slots, PRACH was being scheduled even when the PRACH symbols fell outside the UL portion of the slot. This led to incorrect resource block allocation and scheduling constraint violations that could be observed as:\n- PRACH transmission failures\n- gNB rejecting PRACH due to symbol misalignment\n- UE unable to complete random access procedure\n\nThe issue can be reproduced by configuring a UE with TDD mixed slot configuration where PRACH occasions overlap with DL symbols in the mixed slot.\n"
}